Identity theft accounts for about half of the $1.5 billion in credit card theft in 1995, according to the Secret Service, which monitors the crime.
Identity theft, one of the fastest growing crimes in the nation, is a type of fraud in which a criminal takes another's personal information and uses it to apply for credit.
Identity theft is a crime that evolves with every advance in technology.
Identity theft also became a federal felony this year, punishable by up to 15 years in prison.
